collection.description:
The first 10,000 Sipherians, SIPHER, are the combination of two ideals: Surrogates and Cipher. These are the adventurers in the world of Sipheria. The first of the races, INU, make up the 1st Fleet of the "Sipherian Surge," and were created by mad scientists as a product of animal CRISPR-genome extraction and ethereal elements. Each of these 10,000 INUs possesses unique features, sub-racial traits, and abilities for the mission to establish the first World Block in Sipheria.

Rare sub-race traits are available as BioZ, Cyborg or Cosmic. These are limited with a cap for each type at 1500, 1000 and 500 respectively. Each sub-trait carries unique abilities that impact gameplay and rewards.

The Sipherian Surge 1st Fleet come with a random mix of rare costumes and weapons, allowing each adventurer to assemble a uniquely rare costume set. Costumes will determine attributes buffs, while weapons will determine the class of the character. A complete costume set will grant special attributes.

# Châlet N° 5 | 2017

## Galgenen, Schwyz

collection.description:
The first buyer of each individual NFT from the Chalet Series is eligible for a physical photo book about the series that will be published coming October 2021 by german photobook publisher Hartmann Books. The value of each book is 48€.

Each NFT from the collection comes with GPS coordinates of the original location, so that you can go and visit the place in the future and find out if the building was destroyed or renovated in the meantime. This makes the series a true historic snapshot of Switzerland, captured on the blockchain for eternity. 

Contributors to the photobook are:
Daniel Blochwitz - Curator / Text
Edwin Huwyler - Former scientific lead of the Ballenberg Farmhouse Museum in Switzerland / Text
SYB - BookDesign and concept

All photographs from the series are also available as original limited edition framed prints
Please visit my website for more information on the series.
collection.name: Chalets of Switzerland

On September 10, 2021, the Grey Disclosures 51 paper was released by the Pentagon. It confirmed the existence of aliens among us, camouflaged carefully into the civilian population. Their goal: A full-scale invasion and colonization of planet Earth (that’s our planet, for those of you who don’t have a PhD in astronomy). There are currently 10,000 Invaders among us. We are reaching out to you, the civilian population, for help. You must capture an alien and hold it in your wallet for further study. Our planet will not be safe until they’re all neutralized.

The future of life as we know it depends on you...

collection.description:
The first 10,000 Sipherians, SIPHER, are the combination of two ideals: Surrogates and Cipher. These are the adventurers in the world of Sipheria. The first of the races, INU, make up the 1st Fleet of the "Sipherian Surge," and were created by mad scientists as a product of animal CRISPR-genome extraction and ethereal elements. Each of these 10,000 INUs possesses unique features, sub-racial traits, and abilities for the mission to establish the first World Block in Sipheria.

Rare sub-race traits are available as BioZ, Cyborg or Cosmic. These are limited with a cap for each type at 1500, 1000 and 500 respectively. Each sub-trait carries unique abilities that impact gameplay and rewards.

The Sipherian Surge 1st Fleet come with a random mix of rare costumes and weapons, allowing each adventurer to assemble a uniquely rare costume set. Costumes will determine attributes buffs, while weapons will determine the class of the character. A complete costume set will grant special attributes.

assets.name: CryptoEye 309 of 666
assets.description:
"CrytoEye is an NFT collection created by a reputable scientist whose research output is currently in use in clinics globally. Each CrytoEye has a size of 18 x 37 pixels containing a total of 666 pixels. In addition, there are a total of 666 unique digital collectables generated programmatically using MATLAB, a proprietary-paradigm programming language and numeric computing environment. Unlike python scripts that generate pixel art, these eyes did not rely on base layers but instead generated through matrix manipulation of binary numbers. No two are exactly alike, an each can be owned by a single person. 

The CrytoEye was inspired by The Eye on the one-dollar bill, one of the most powerful symbols known to many cultures that can indicate good, evil, wisdom, protection, knowledge, secrecy and mystery. The number 666, another multicultural symbol, is used by Chinese gamers to commend skilful play. On the other hand, 666 is cryptically referred to as the “mark”, “name” or “number” of Beast, said to mark the forehead or the right hand of all who buy or sell, interpreted as a symbol for Roman Empire. It is the first instance of the Eye used in a generative art project with custom on-chain and cryptographically secure provenance."

collection.description:
The first 10,000 Sipherians, SIPHER, are the combination of two ideals: Surrogates and Cipher. These are the adventurers in the world of Sipheria. The first of the races, INU, make up the 1st Fleet of the "Sipherian Surge," and were created by mad scientists as a product of animal CRISPR-genome extraction and ethereal elements. Each of these 10,000 INUs possesses unique features, sub-racial traits, and abilities for the mission to establish the first World Block in Sipheria.

Rare sub-race traits are available as BioZ, Cyborg or Cosmic. These are limited with a cap for each type at 1500, 1000 and 500 respectively. Each sub-trait carries unique abilities that impact gameplay and rewards.

The Sipherian Surge 1st Fleet come with a random mix of rare costumes and weapons, allowing each adventurer to assemble a uniquely rare costume set. Costumes will determine attributes buffs, while weapons will determine the class of the character. A complete costume set will grant special attributes.
collection.name: SipherianSurge(Offical)

collection.description: Kittens Against Cancer is an NFT collection generated to support cancer treatment and research.  It will consist of 15,000 unique Kitten NFTs, with no two the same.  A 100% of the proceeds of the initial sale (less taxes and fees) will go to cancer charities.  Further 50% of royalties from future resales will similarly be donated to support cancer treatment and research.  Hopefully, this will help to inspire people and use this platform to serve the greater good while supporting art.  Expecting an Early-Mid September Launch.  Ultimately it would be great if $1,000,000 could be raised in support of Cancer Charities, an issue that strikes close to home for me and I am sure many others.
